Subject: [PATCH] pango_display: do not compile embedded fonts twice

`pango_opengl` already generates and owns `fonts.cpp` (AnonymousPro_ttf*).
`pango_display` links against `pango_opengl`, so compiling `fonts.cpp` again in
`pango_display` duplicates the same global font blob symbols across DSOs and
triggers ASAN ODR violations.

Keep the embedded fonts in `pango_opengl` only and let `pango_display`
reference the symbols through that dependency.
---
 components/pango_display/CMakeLists.txt | 1 -
 1 file changed, 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/components/pango_display/CMakeLists.txt b/components/pango_display/CMakeLists.txt
index 79e40b1..d411144 100644
--- a/components/pango_display/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/components/pango_display/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -13,7 +13,6 @@ PRIVATE
     ${CMAKE_CURRENT_LIST_DIR}/src/image_view.cpp
     ${CMAKE_CURRENT_LIST_DIR}/src/ConsoleView.cpp
     ${CMAKE_CURRENT_LIST_DIR}/src/default_font.cpp
-    ${CMAKE_CURRENT_BINARY_DIR}/fonts.cpp
 )
 
